Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Soak the @bamboo skewers{4} in cold water (this will prevent them from burning).

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{}, season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake the chips on the middle shelf until golden, ~{30-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, quarter and peel the @red onion{1}(quartered and peeled), then separate the layers.

Drain the @king prawns{150%g}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns.

Carefully thread the prawns and onion layers onto #skewers{} (2 per person) carefully alternating between the two.

Drizzle over some @olive oil{} and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Pop on a large baking tray lined with #foil{}.

When turning the chips halfway through, pop your skewers on the top shelf of your oven to cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

While the skewers and chips cook, trim the @baby gem lettuce{1}(trimmed and halved lengthways), then thinly slice.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the @mayonnaise{32%g}, @sambal paste{15%g}(to taste), @sugar{1%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing.

> Add less sambal if you'd prefer things milder.

Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

Crush the @salted peanuts{25%g} in the unopened sachet using a #rolling pin{}.

== Honey-Gochujang Sauce ==

Pop a #small saucepan{} on medium-low heat. Add the @gochujang paste{30%g}(to taste) and @honey{15%g}.

> Add less gochujang if you'd prefer things milder.

Stir together and simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in the @butter{20%g} until melted. This is your honey-gochujang sauce.

== Assembly ==

Just before everything's ready, toss the salad through the sambal dressing.

Share the skewers between your #plates{}. Drizzle the honey-gochujang sauce over each skewer.

Serve the sambal salad and chips alongside, along with some @tomato ketchup{3%tbsp} for dipping.

Sprinkle the crushed peanuts over the sambal salad to finish. Enjoy!